{{Infobox accounting body |name_in_local_language= <!--Give name in other languages. Page name will be added as English name automatically --> |abbreviation = SAIPA |image = SAIPA (SA) logo.jpg |image_border = |alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> |image_caption = <!-- caption of the above image --> |motto = Your Wealth |predecessor = <!-- Name of any predecessor entity if any --> |formation = <!-- give in format {{Start date and years ago|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> |legal_status = <!-- society, statutory body corporate, company, etc --> |objective = Encourage professionalism in accountancy |headquarters = Midrand, {{flag|South Africa}} |coords = <!-- Coordinates of headquarters using {{coord}} --> |region_served = South Africa |membership_num = > 13 000 |students_num = <!-- No of students --> |members_designations = <!--give the various designations awarded to the members like ACA, FCA, etc.. --> |language = <!-- official languages --> |highest_officer_title = Executive Chairman |highest_officer_name = Shafiek Dollie |second_officer_title = Deputy Chairperson |second_officer_name = Kantha Naicker |fourth_officer_title = <!-- position of the fourth ranking officer like Treasurer, CFO etc.. --> |fourth_officer_name = <!-- name of the above person --> |administering_organ = <!-- Council, General Body, Board of Directors, etc --> |IFAC_membership_date = <!-- Date when the body became an IFAC member if it is one --> |additional_data_name1 = <!-- Optional data1 name --> |additional_data1 = <!-- Optional data1 --> |additional_data_name2 = <!-- Optional data2 name --> |additional_data2 = <!-- Optional data2 --> |additional_data_name3 = <!-- Optional data3 name --> |additional_data3 = <!-- Optional data2 --> |num_staff = |website = {{url|http://www.saipa.co.za/}} |remarks = |former name = Institute of Certified Public Accountants of South Africa }}
The '''South African Institute of Professional Accountants''' (SAIPA) is a professional association of accountants based in [[South Africa]]. {{As of|2016}}, the institute had more than 10,000 members.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.saipa.co.za/page/658/benefits-membership |title=BENEFITS OF MEMBERSHIP |publisher=SAIPA |accessdate=25 July 2016}}</ref>
==Qualification== The requirements for membership are:<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.saipa.co.za/DisplayContent.asp?ContentPageID=261 |title = GENERAL INFORMATION ON THE PE |publisher = SAIPA |accessdate = 2012-01-26 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110212205843/http://www.saipa.co.za/DisplayContent.asp?ContentPageID=261# |archive-date = 2011-02-12 |dead-url = yes |df = }}</ref> *Academic: A Degree with a [[Academic major|major]] in [[financial accounting]] and with [[tax]], [[management accounting]], [[auditing]] and [[commercial law]] as subjects. *Practical training or experience: at least 3 years under a SAIPA recognised Learnership, or 6 years of relevant verifiable experience. *SAIPA Professional Evaluation: This is a three-hour examination offered twice yearly covering [http://www.saipa.co.za/documents/SAIPA%20PE%20Learner%20Guide%20-TD01-V2.pdf]{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Financial Accounting, Auditing, Taxation, Commercial Law, Management Accounting and Practice Management.
==Associated organizations== SAIPA is a full member of the [[International Federation of Accountants]] (IFAC) and the [[Pan African Federation of Accountants]] (PAFA). SAIPA has reciprocal agreements with national and international bodies. Members of foreign bodies wishing to become a member of SAIPA and who wish to practice in South Africa have to meet the full membership requirements of SAIPA in all respects. A reciprocal membership agreement alone may not allow anyone to practice in South Africa until these requirements are met. (IAAER).<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.iaaer.org/about/institutions.htm |title = Institutional Members |publisher = IAAER |accessdate = 2011-06-30 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20111227165908/http://www.iaaer.org/about/institutions.htm |archivedate = 2011-12-27 |df = }}</ref> SAIPA members are eligible for membership of the Institute of Accounting and Commerce.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iacsa.co.za/index.php?page=pages&pid=41 |title=CRITERIA FOR ADMISSION TO PROFESSIONAL MEMBERSHIP |work=Institute of Accounting and Commerce |accessdate=2011-06-30}}</ref>
